idinfo.useconst: Office of the Minnesota Secretary of State maintains this data as accurately as possible, but cannot assure 100% accuracy. For definitive precinct lines, please contact the jurisdiction (city, township, or county for unorganized territory) in question. To check precinct and districts or find polling place for an address, use the Secretary of State's Polling Place Finder: http://pollfinder.sos.state.mn.us.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Vote Tabulation District Identifier, used by U.S. Census Bureau. Concatenates State FIPS code (27), COUNTYFIPS, and PCTCODE
Four digit code assigned to precinct (unique within each county)
Abbreviated PCTNAME for labelling purposes. In most cases indicates a jurisdiction with multiple precincts
Municipality (city or town) that the precinct is in. For unorganized territories, MCD name may not match the U.S. Census name and/or boundary for an MCD.
Jurisdiction's FIPS code (note: some unorganized area FIPS codes may be manufactured)
Jurisdiction's Geographic Names Information System (GNIS) code
Minnesota House District. House districts A & B nest together within the corresponding Senate district
County Commissioner District. Most counties have 5. Anoka, Dakota, Hennepin, Olmsted, Ramsey, and St. Louis have 7.

Soil & Water Conservation District Code. The supervisors are usually voted on by the entire county, except the following cases. Hennepin and Ramsey counties have each transfered these powers to the county board and disbanded the SWCD. Otter Tail (East and West) and St. Louis (North and South) Counties are split into two separate districts. In Anoka, Carver, Dakota, Renville, Scott, and Washington Counties, the 5 SWCD supervisors are all elected by supervisor district.
Park District code, There are only two park districts: Minneapolis and Three Rivers (Hennepin County outside of Minneapolis)
Area of feature in internal units squared.

horizpa.horizpar: The positional accuracy of the precinct boundaries is generally the same as the sources the precinct datasets were orignally derived from--see https://gisdata.mn.gov/dataset/bdry-mn-city-township-unorg

procstep.procdesc: Boundaries derived from Minnesota's City, Township, and Unorganized Territory (CTU) Boundaries dataset (2013) and U.S. Census redistricting data. Boundaries incorporate election district boundary corrections made under MS 2.91, subd. 2 and MS 204B.146, subd. 3, and municipal boundary adjustments that were effective through December 1, 2019.

dataqual.logic: Topology checks run to try to eliminate gaps and overlaps betweeen polygons.

attracc.attraccr: Precinct and district attributes from Statewide Voter Registration System (SVRS).
